Explanation1:
\begin{aligned}
&\text{Using general term formulae $T_{r+1}={ }^n C_rx^{n-r}y^r$}\\
&\text{The general term is} \\
&T_{r+1}={ }^{11} C_r(a x^2)^{11-r}\left(\frac{1}{bx}\right)^r \\
&T_{r+1}={ }^{11} C_r a^{11-r} ~~b^{-r} ~x^{22-3 r} \\
\end{aligned}

Explanation2:
\begin{aligned}
&T_{5+1} \text { or the } 6 \text {th term will contain } x^7 \text {. }\\
&T_6={ }^{11} C_5\left(a x^2\right)^{11-5}\left(\frac{1}{b x}\right)^5\\
&=\frac{11 \times 10 \times 9 \times 8 \times 7}{5 !} \frac{a^6}{b^5} x^7=\frac{462 a^6}{b^5} x^7\\
&\text { Hence the coefficient of } x^7 \text { is } \frac{462 a^6}{b^5} \text {. }
\end{aligned}
